Olson Industries Inc saidit is in final negotiations on the sale of its remaining eggoperations and expects the sale to generate a charge of abouttwo mln dlrs against 1987 net income.    The company said, however, that the sale will generatesubstantial cash flow to pay off bank debt and improve workingcapital, eliminate unmanageable effects on profits of the priceinstability of the egg business and allow it to concentrate onits plastics packaging business. Reuter&#3;